description.p:
According to another embodiment of this aspect of the invention, the method involves assigning the operation state to:
operating the camera at the high frame rate, if the test parameter indicates that the eye image from the camera fulfills a first operation criterion;
operating the camera at the reduced frame rate, if the test parameter indicates that the eye image from the camera fulfills a second operation criterion, however not the first operation criterion;
the standby mode, if the test parameter indicates that the eye image from the camera fulfills a third operation criterion, however neither the first nor the second operation criterion; and
be powered off, if the test parameter indicates that the eye image from the camera does not fulfil any of the first, second or third operation criteria.
